Not all sunscreens are built the same. A high SPF isn’t enough—photostability matters. If your sunscreen breaks down under UV rays, it stops protecting your skin.

I put Neutrogena Ultra Sheer Sunscreen to the test using a UV patch—and it didn’t just hold up, it proved why it’s a top pick.

With Helioplex XP technology, it gives stable, broad-spectrum protection against UVA, UVB, and blue light, without feeling heavy or leaving a white cast.

Your sunscreen should work as hard as you do—this one does.
